{
  "texts": [
    "It also encapsulates criteria indicating the start and termination of the process, along with details concerning participants, IT systems, and data [23].",
    "Several process models have been proposed in recent years [24] within their application in real domains [25,26].",
    "Among the simplest notations for representing a business process lies the Directly-Follows Graph (DFG) [27].",
    "This graphical representation comprises nodes denoting individual activities, while directed arcs delineate the sequential relationships between them, signifying direct succession.Another common modeling language for business processes is Business Processing Modeling Notation (BPMN).",
    "It is a standard language, proposed by the Object Management Group (OMG), to design business processes [9]."
  ]
}